31/01/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The Romanian Defence Ministry and the Centre for Nuclear, Biological and Chemical Surveillance launched a new system for automatic collection and distribution of data Thursday (30 January).
The new equipment would provide early warning analyses and options for resolving critical situations, and would monitor the country with a special focus on arrears surrounding chemical and nuclear enterprises.
Also Thursday, representatives of the defence ministry announced that the Romanian Air Force concluded the purchase of 21 modern military radars and would buy 50 new fighting jets next year.
(Rompres, Nine o'Clock - 31/01/03)
